Usage: pyloc.py directory [-v]

Where directory is the directory to scan and -v will cause verbose output.

Example basic output:
---------------------

[james@collingwood pyloc]$ ./pyloc.py /home/james/projects-git/haskellhead/

    PYLOC
    -----
    Folder   : /home/james/projects-git/haskellhead/

    Summary
    -------
    Haskell: 99.04%
    Shell: 0.96%

    TOTAL physical SLOC : 1775

Example verbose output:
-----------------------

[james@collingwood pyloc]$ ./pyloc.py /home/james/projects-git/haskellhead/ -v

    PYLOC
    -----
    Folder   : /home/james/projects-git/haskellhead/

    Language : Shell
            Files         : 1
            Code lines    : 12
            Comment lines : 1
            Whitespace    : 4

            Physical SLOC : 17

    Language : Haskell
            Files         : 15
            Code lines    : 1326
            Comment lines : 150
            Whitespace    : 282

            Physical SLOC : 1758

    Summary
    -------
    Haskell: 99.04%
    Shell: 0.96%

    TOTAL physical SLOC : 1775

